What are the basic control flow statements in Go?
| Category       | Statement                                            | Purpose                            |
| -------------- | ---------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| Conditional    | `if`, `else if`, `else`                              | Make decisions based on conditions |
| Looping        | `for`, `range`                                       | Repeat execution                   |
| Jump/Branching | `break`, `continue`, `goto`, `fallthrough`, `return` | Control loop or function behavior  |
| Switch-case    | `switch`, `case`, `default`                          | Multiple conditional branches      |
